{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879565057,"sessionID":"ses_2855485c2ffeiU9p9SZjJiSl0T","part":{"id":"prt_d7aab9a9d001s2pSkFtTwsagNk","messageID":"msg_d7aab8fad001Hyxrul0rkBuhU9","sessionID":"ses_2855485c2ffeiU9p9SZjJiSl0T","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b6f36ff93f6f4d618d962e06","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `manifests`  \n6: **Language:** YAML  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Type:** Helm Chart implementation for AgentCube control plane components\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md, deployment/design.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-030.1: Chart.yaml Metadata\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Chart.yaml with apiVersion v1, name agentcube, version 0.1.0, and appVersion 1.0.0.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure\n21: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** Chart.yaml is created\n23: - **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n24:   - `apiVersion: v1`\n25:   - `name: agentcube`\n26:   - `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n27:   - `version: 0.1.0`\n28:   - `appVersion: \"1.0.0\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Chart metadata keywords\n31: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n32: - **WHEN** metadata is defined\n33: - **THEN** keywords SHALL include: `agent`, `sandbox`, `kubernetes`, `volcano`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Chart maintainers\n36: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n37: - **WHEN** maintainers are defined\n38: - **THEN** maintainers SHALL include Volcano Authors with email `volcano-sh@googlegroups.com`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Chart home and sources\n41: - **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n42: - **WHEN** home and sources are defined\n43: - **THEN** they SHALL reference `https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### REQ-030.2: values.yaml Configuration Tree\n48: \n49: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement values.yaml with complete configuration tree for Redis, Router, WorkloadManager, and Volcano Scheduler.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Redis configuration\n52: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n53: - **WHEN** redis configuration is defined\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n55:   - `redis.addr: \"\"` (empty default, user must provide)\n56:   - `redis.password: \"\"` (empty default for non-auth Redis)\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Router replicas and image\n59: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n60: - **WHEN** router configuration is defined\n61: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n62:   - `router.replicas: 1`\n63:   - `router.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router`\n64:   - `router.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n65:   - `router.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Router service configuration\n68: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n69: - **WHEN** router service is defined\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n71:   - `router.service.type: ClusterIP`\n72:   - `router.service.port: 8080`\n73:   - `router.service.targetPort: 8080`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Router resources\n76: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n77: - **WHEN** router resources are defined\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n79:   - `router.resources.limits.cpu: 500m`\n80:   - `router.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi`\n81:   - `router.resources.requests.cpu: 100m`\n82:   - `router.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi`\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Router RBAC toggle\n85: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n86: - **WHEN** router.rbac configuration is defined\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n88:   - `router.rbac.create: false` (disabled by default)\n89:   - `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` (empty for auto-generated or default)\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager replicas and image\n92: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n93: - **WHEN** workloadmanager configuration is defined\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n95:   - `workloadmanager.replicas: 1`\n96:   - `workloadmanager.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager`\n97:   - `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n98:   - `workloadmanager.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager service configuration\n101: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n102: - **WHEN** workloadmanager service is defined\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n104:   - `workloadmanager.service.type: ClusterIP`\n105:   - `workloadmanager.service.port: 8080`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager resources\n108: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n109: - **WHEN** workloadmanager resources are defined\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n111:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 500m`\n112:   - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi`\n113:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu: 100m`\n114:   - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi`\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager extraEnv\n117: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n118: - **WHEN** workloadmanager.extraEnv is defined\n119: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` for additional environment variables\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler enabled toggle\n122: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n123: - **WHEN** volcano.scheduler configuration is defined\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n125:   - `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (disabled by default)\n126:   - `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 1`\n127:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler`\n128:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n129:   - `volcano.scheduler.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Image pull secrets\n132: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n133: - **WHEN** imagePullSecrets is defined\n134: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` by default\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Name overrides\n137: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n138: - **WHEN** nameOverride and fullnameOverride are defined\n139: - **THEN** they SHALL be empty strings `\"\"` by default\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Router extraEnv\n142: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n143: - **WHEN** router.extraEnv is defined\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` for additional environment variables\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Router config\n147: - **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n148: - **WHEN** router.config is defined\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL be an empty object `{}` for additional container configuration\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### REQ-030.3: Workload Manager Deployment Template\n154: \n155: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Workload Manager Deployment template with correct environment variables, probes, and resource configuration.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Deployment metadata\n158: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n159: - **WHEN** Workload Manager Deployment is created\n160: - **THEN** metadata SHALL include:\n161:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n162:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n163:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Workload Manager replicas from values\n166: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.replicas: 2`\n167: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n168: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `2`\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image from values\n171: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has custom image repository\n172: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n173: - **THEN** container image SHALL be `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Workload Manager environment variables\n176: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n177: - **WHEN** container env is defined\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n179:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from fieldRef `metadata.namespace`\n180:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}`\n181:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from Secret `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password`\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Workload Manager extraEnv injection\n184: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.extraEnv` entries\n185: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n186: - **THEN** extraEnv entries SHALL be injected into container env\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Workload Manager args\n189: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n190: - **WHEN** container args are defined\n191: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n192:   - `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n193:   - `--runtime-class-name=` (empty)\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Workload Manager liveness probe\n196: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n197: - **WHEN** livenessProbe is defined\n198: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n199:   - `httpGet.path: /health`\n200:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n201:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 10`\n202:   - `periodSeconds: 10`\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Workload Manager readiness probe\n205: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n206: - **WHEN** readinessProbe is defined\n207: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n208:   - `httpGet.path: /health`\n209:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n210:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 5`\n211:   - `periodSeconds: 5`\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Workload Manager resources from values\n214: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.resources` defined\n215: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n216: - **THEN** `resources` SHALL be rendered from values using `toYaml`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image pull secrets\n219: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `imagePullSecrets` entries\n220: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n221: - **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` SHALL be injected into pod spec\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Workload Manager service account\n224: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n225: - **WHEN** serviceAccountName is defined\n226: - **THEN** it SHALL be `workloadmanager`\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Service\n229: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n230: - **WHEN** Workload Manager Service is created\n231: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n232:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n233:   - `type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}`\n234:   - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n235:   - `targetPort: http`\n236:   - Selector: `app: workloadmanager`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ### REQ-030.4: Router Deployment Template\n241: \n242: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Router Deployment template with correct environment variables, probes, and WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL.\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: Router Deployment metadata\n245: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n246: - **WHEN** Router Deployment is created\n247: - **THEN** metadata SHALL include:\n248:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n249:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n250:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Router replicas from values\n253: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.replicas: 3`\n254: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n255: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `3`\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Router image from values\n258: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has custom router image\n259: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n260: - **THEN** container image SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}`\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Router environment variables\n263: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n264: - **WHEN** container env is defined\n265: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n266:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from fieldRef `metadata.namespace`\n267:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}`\n268:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from Secret `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password`\n269:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"`\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Router extraEnv injection\n272: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.extraEnv` entries\n273: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n274: - **THEN** extraEnv entries SHALL be injected into container env\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Router args\n277: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n278: - **WHEN** container args are defined\n279: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n280:   - `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n281:   - `--debug`\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: Router liveness probe\n284: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n285: - **WHEN** livenessProbe is defined\n286: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n287:   - `httpGet.path: /health/live`\n288:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n289:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 1`\n290:   - `periodSeconds: 2`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Router readiness probe\n293: - **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n294: - **WHEN** readinessProbe is defined\n295: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n296:   - `httpGet.path: /health/ready`\n297:   - `httpGet.port: http`\n298:   - `initialDelaySeconds: 1`\n299:   - `periodSeconds: 2`\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Router service account conditional\n302: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.serviceAccountName: \"custom-sa\"`\n303: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n304: - **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL be `custom-sa`\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: Router service account empty\n307: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"`\n308: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n309: - **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL NOT be set (use default)\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Router Service\n312: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n313: - **WHEN** Router Service is created\n314: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n315:   - `name: agentcube-router`\n316:   - `type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}`\n317:   - `port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}`\n318:   - `targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n319:   - Selector: `app: agentcube-router`\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ### REQ-030.5: Workload Manager RBAC\n324: \n325: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Workload Manager RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) with correct permissions.\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ServiceAccount\n328: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n329: - **WHEN** Workload Manager ServiceAccount is created\n330: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n331:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n332:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n333:   - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole sandbox permissions\n336: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n337: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n338: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n339:   - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`, `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole extension resources\n342: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n343: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n344: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n345:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n346:   - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n347:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole warm pool status\n350: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n351: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n352: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n353:   - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n354:   - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n355:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n358: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n359: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n360: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n361:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n362:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n363:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n364:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n365:   - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`, `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n368: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n369: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n370: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n371:   - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n372:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n373:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n374:   - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n375:   - `verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]`\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole pod permissions\n378: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n379: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n380: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n381:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n382:   - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n383:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole token review\n386: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n387: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n388: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n389:   - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n390:   - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n391:   - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole secret permissions\n394: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n395: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n396: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n397:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n398:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n399:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding\n402: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n403: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is created\n404: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n405:   - `name: workloadmanager`\n406:   - Subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: workloadmanager`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n407:   - RoleRef: `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: workloadmanager`, `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ### REQ-030.6: Router RBAC (Optional)\n412: \n413: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement optional Router RBAC resources controlled by `router.rbac.create` flag.\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: Router RBAC disabled by default\n416: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.rbac.create: false`\n417: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n418: - **THEN** Router RBAC resources SHALL NOT be created\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled\n421: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.rbac.create: true`\n422: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n423: - **THEN** Router ServiceAccount, Role, and RoleBinding SHALL be created\n424: \n425: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount name\n426: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n427: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n428: - **THEN** name SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: Router Role secret permissions\n431: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n432: - **WHEN** Role rules are defined\n433: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n434:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n435:   - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n436:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: Router RoleBinding\n439: - **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n440: - **WHEN** RoleBinding is created\n441: - **THEN** it SHALL reference:\n442:   - Subject: ServiceAccount with default name\n443:   - RoleRef: Role with same name\n444: \n445: ---\n446: \n447: ### REQ-030.7: Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n448: \n449: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement optional Volcano Agent Scheduler resources controlled by `volcano.scheduler.enabled` flag.\n450: \n451: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler disabled by default\n452: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false`\n453: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n454: - **THEN** Volcano Scheduler resources SHALL NOT be created\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler enabled\n457: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n458: - **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n459: - **THEN** ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, and Deployment SHALL be created\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n462: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n463: - **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n464: - **THEN** name SHALL be `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n465: \n466: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ConfigMap\n467: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n468: - **WHEN** ConfigMap is created\n469: - **THEN** it SHALL include `agent-scheduler.conf` with:\n470:   - `actions: \"allocate\"`\n471:   - `tiers:` with `plugins: \"predicates,nodeorder\"`\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole CRD permissions\n474: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n475: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n476: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n477:   - `apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]`\n478:   - `resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]`\n479:   - `verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]`\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole pod permissions\n482: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n483: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n484: - **THEN** it SHALL include comprehensive pod permissions:\n485:   - `pods`, `pods/status`, `pods/binding`, `pods/disruptionbudgets`\n486:   - `persistentvolumeclaims`, `persistentvolumes`\n487:   - `nodes`, `namespaces`, `services`, `replicationcontrollers`\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole scheduling permissions\n490: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n491: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n492: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n493:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.k8s.io\"]`\n494:   - `resources: [\"priorityclasses\"]`\n495:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n496:   - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.incubator.k8s.io\", \"scheduling.volcano.sh\"]`\n497:   - `resources: [\"podgroups\"]`\n498:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\", \"update\"]`\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole storage permissions\n501: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n502: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n503: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n504:   - `apiGroups: [\"storage.k8s.io\"]`\n505:   - `resources: [\"storageclasses\", \"csinodes\", \"csidrivers\", \"csistoragecapacities\", \"volumeattachments\"]`\n506:   - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\"]`\n507: \n508: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole configmap permissions\n509: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n510: - **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n511: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n512:   - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n513:   - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n514:   - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"update\"]`\n515: \n516: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n517: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n518: - **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is created\n519: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n520:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler-role`\n521:   - Subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n522:   - RoleRef: `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Service\n525: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n526: - **WHEN** Service is created\n527: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n528:   - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler-service`\n529:   - `port: 8080`, `targetPort: 8080`, `name: metrics`\n530:   - Annotations: `prometheus.io/scrape: \"true\"`, `prometheus.io/port: \"8080\"`\n531:   - Selector: `app: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n532: \n533: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Deployment args\n534: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n535: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n536: - **THEN** container args SHALL include:\n537:   - `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`\n538:   - `--config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf`\n539: \n540: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Deployment volumes\n541: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n542: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n543: - **THEN** it SHALL include volumes:\n544:   - `name: config`, `configMap.name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap`\n545:   - `name: empty`, `emptyDir: {}`\n546: \n547: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler security context\n548: - **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n549: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n550: - **THEN** container securityContext SHALL include:\n551:   - `runAsNonRoot: true`\n552:   - `runAsUser: 1000`\n553: \n554: #### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler replicas from values\n555: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 2`\n556: - **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n557: - **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `2`\n558: \n559: ---\n560: \n561: ### REQ-030.8: Redis Secret Template\n562: \n563: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Redis Secret template to store Redis password.\n564: \n565: #### Scenario: Redis Secret creation\n566: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n567: - **WHEN** Redis Secret is created\n568: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n569:   - `name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis`\n570:   - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n571:   - `type: Opaque`\n572: \n573: #### Scenario: Redis Secret data\n574: - **GIVEN** values.yaml has `redis.password: \"mysecret\"`\n575: - **WHEN** Secret is rendered\n576: - **THEN** `stringData.password` SHALL be `\"mysecret\"`\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Redis Secret labels\n579: - **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n580: - **WHEN** Secret labels are defined\n581: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n582:   - `app.kubernetes.io/name: redis`\n583:   - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n584: \n585: ---\n586: \n587: ### REQ-030.9: CRD Files\n588: \n589: **Requirement:** The system SHALL include CRD files for agentruntimes and codeinterpreters.\n590: \n591: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD existence\n592: - **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n593: - **WHEN** CRDs are applied\n594: - **THEN** `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` SHALL be created\n595: \n596: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD group and version\n597: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CRD is applied\n598: - **WHEN** CRD spec is validated\n599: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n600:   - `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n601:   - `spec.versions[0].name: v1alpha1`\n602: \n603: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD existence\n604: - **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n605: - **WHEN** CRDs are applied\n606: - **THEN** `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` SHALL be created\n607: \n608: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD group and version\n609: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreter CRD is applied\n610: - **WHEN** CRD spec is validated\n611: - **THEN** it SHALL include:\n612:   - `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n613:   - `spec.versions[0].name: v1alpha1`\n614: \n615: #### Scenario: CRD installation order\n616: - **GIVEN** helm install is run\n617: - **WHEN** chart is installed\n618: - **THEN** CRDs SHALL be installed before other resources\n619: \n620: ---\n621: \n622: ### REQ-030.10: .helmignore\n623: \n624: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement .helmignore file to exclude unnecessary files from chart packaging.\n625: \n626: #### Scenario: Git files ignored\n627: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n628: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n629: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.git/`, `.gitignore`\n630: \n631: #### Scenario: Version control files ignored\n632: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n633: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n634: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.bzr/`, `.bzrignore`, `.hg/`, `.hgignore`, `.svn/`\n635: \n636: #### Scenario: Temporary files ignored\n637: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n638: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n639: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `*.swp`, `*.bak`, `*.tmp`, `*.orig`, `*~`\n640: \n641: #### Scenario: IDE files ignored\n642: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n643: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n644: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `.project`, `.idea/`, `*.tmproj`, `.vscode/`\n645: \n646: #### Scenario: Test files ignored\n647: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n648: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n649: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `tests/`\n650: \n651: #### Scenario: Documentation files ignored\n652: - **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n653: - **WHEN** patterns are defined\n654: - **THEN** it SHALL include: `*.md` but NOT `!README.md`\n655: \n656: ---\n657: \n658: ### REQ-030.11: Helm Lint and Template Validation\n659: \n660: **Requirement:** The system SHALL pass `helm lint` without errors and `helm template` shall generate valid YAML.\n661: \n662: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n663: - **GIVEN** chart structure is complete\n664: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is run\n665: - **THEN** it SHALL return no errors\n666: \n667: #### Scenario: Helm template generates valid YAML\n668: - **GIVEN** chart structure is complete\n669: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n670: - **THEN** output SHALL be valid YAML that can be parsed\n671: \n672: #### Scenario: Helm template with custom values\n673: - **GIVEN** custom values file is provided\n674: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base -f custom-values.yaml` is run\n675: - **THEN** output SHALL reflect custom values overrides\n676: \n677: #### Scenario: Helm template with Volcano enabled\n678: - **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` is passed\n679: - **WHEN** `helm template` is run\n680: - **THEN** output SHALL include Volcano Scheduler resources\n681: \n682: #### Scenario: Helm template with Router RBAC enabled\n683: - **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true` is passed\n684: - **WHEN** `helm template` is run\n685: - **THEN** output SHALL include Router RBAC resources\n686: \n687: ---\n688: \n689: ### REQ-030.12: Multi-Environment Support\n690: \n691: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support multi-environment deployment through values overrides.\n692: \n693: #### Scenario: Development environment values\n694: - **GIVEN** development values file is provided\n695: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `-f values-dev.yaml`\n696: - **THEN** all components SHALL use development-appropriate settings (e.g., lower resources)\n697: \n698: #### Scenario: Production environment values\n699: - **GIVEN** production values file is provided\n700: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `-f values-prod.yaml`\n701: - **THEN** all components SHALL use production-appropriate settings (e.g., higher replicas, resources)\n702: \n703: #### Scenario: Region-specific Redis configuration\n704: - **GIVEN** different regions have different Redis addresses\n705: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `--set redis.addr=redis-region1.svc:6379`\n706: - **THEN** components SHALL connect to specified Redis address\n707: \n708: #### Scenario: Custom image repository override\n709: - **GIVEN** organization uses private registry\n710: - **WHEN** helm install is run with `--set router.image.repository=myregistry.com/router`\n711: - **THEN** Router SHALL use custom image repository\n712: \n713: ---\n714: \n715: ## Data Types\n716: \n717: ```yaml\n718: # values.yaml structure\n719: values:\n720:   imagePullSecrets: []\n721:   nameOverride: \"\"\n722:   fullnameOverride: \"\"\n723:   \n724:   redis:\n725:     addr: string       # Required: Redis address\n726:     password: string   # Optional: Redis password\n727:   \n728:   router:\n729:     replicas: int\n730:     image:\n731:       repository: string\n732:       pullPolicy: string\n733:       tag: string\n734:     service:\n735:       type: string\n736:       port: int\n737:       targetPort: int\n738:     resources:\n739:       limits:\n740:         cpu: string\n741:         memory: string\n742:       requests:\n743:         cpu: string\n744:         memory: string\n745:     config: object\n746:     extraEnv: []\n747:     serviceAccountName: string\n748:     rbac:\n749:       create: bool\n750:   \n751:   workloadmanager:\n752:     replicas: int\n753:     image:\n754:       repository: string\n755:       pullPolicy: string\n756:       tag: string\n757:     service:\n758:       type: string\n759:       port: int\n760:     resources:\n761:       limits:\n762:         cpu: string\n763:         memory: string\n764:       requests:\n765:         cpu: string\n766:         memory: string\n767:     extraEnv: []\n768:   \n769:   volcano:\n770:     scheduler:\n771:       enabled: bool\n772:       replicas: int\n773:       image:\n774:         repository: string\n775:         pullPolicy: string\n776:         tag: string\n777: ```\n778: \n779: ---\n780: \n781: ## File Structure\n782: \n783: ```\n784: manifests/charts/base/\n785: ├── Chart.yaml\n786: ├── values.yaml\n787: ├── .helmignore\n788: ├── crds/\n789: │   ├── agentruntime.yaml\n790: │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml\n791: └── templates/\n792:     ├── _helpers.tpl\n793:     ├── redis-secret.yaml\n794:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n795:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n796:     ├── rbac/\n797:     │   └── workloadmanager.yaml\n798:     ├── rbac-router.yaml\n799:     └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml\n800: ```\n801: \n802: ---\n803: \n804: ## Environment Variables\n805: \n806: | Variable | Component | Description | Source |\n807: |----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n808: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Namespace from downward API | fieldRef |\n809: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis address | values.redis.addr |\n810: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis password | Secret |\n811: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager URL | Constructed from values |\n812: \n813: ---\n814: \n815: ## Error Codes\n816: \n817: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n818: |-------|-----------|---------|\n819: | Chart validation failure | 1 | `helm lint` failed: {detail} |\n820: | Template render failure | 1 | `helm template` failed: {detail} |\n821: | CRD installation failure | 1 | Failed to install CRD: {detail} |\n822: | Redis address not provided | 1 | `redis.addr` is required in values |\n823: | Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | YAML parse error in {file}: {detail} |\n824: \n825: ---\n826: \n827: ## Dependencies\n828: \n829: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n830: |---------|---------|---------|\n831: | Helm | ≥3.0 | Chart packaging and deployment |\n832: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | API compatibility |\n833: | Redis | Any | External dependency (session storage) |\n834: \n835: ---\n836: \n837: ## Acceptance Checklist\n838: \n839: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` — Chart metadata with correct apiVersion, name, version\n840: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` — Complete configuration tree for all components\n841: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with correct env/probes\n842: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n843: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n844: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` — Conditional Router RBAC\n845: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — Conditional Volcano Scheduler\n846: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml` — Redis password Secret\n847: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml` — AgentRuntime CRD (existing, verify completeness)\n848: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml` — CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n849: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore` — Ignore patterns for packaging\n850: - [ ] `helm lint` passes without errors\n851: - [ ] `helm template` generates valid YAML\n852: - [ ] `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n853: - [ ] Optional components render correctly when enabled/disabled\n854: - [ ] Values overrides work correctly for multi-environment support\n855: \n856: ---\n857: \n858: ## Open Questions\n859: \n860: 1. Should the chart support external Redis Operator integration?\n861: 2. Should monitoring and logging configurations be integrated into the chart?\n862: 3. Should multi-cluster deployment be supported through values configuration?\n863: 4. Should the chart include default values for development/testing environments?\n\n(End of file - total 863 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** Helm Chart implementation for AgentCube control plane components\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md, deployment/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-030.1: Chart.yaml Metadata\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Chart.yaml with apiVersion v1, name agentcube, version 0.1.0, and appVersion 1.0.0.\n\n#### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879565027,"end":1775879565054}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879565060,"sessionID":"ses_2855485c2ffeiU9p9SZjJiSl0T","part":{"id":"prt_d7aab9fab00175vfUHEHqR4o57","messageID":"msg_d7aab8fad001Hyxrul0rkBuhU9","sessionID":"ses_2855485c2ffeiU9p9SZjJiSl0T","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0c0732a8b8c24bb0a1c6e624","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Chart Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: manifests/charts/base/\n13: ├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n14: ├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n15: ├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n16: ├── crds/\n17: │   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n18: │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n19: └── templates/\n20:     ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions\n21:     ├── redis-secret.yaml               # Redis password Secret\n22:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml            # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n23:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml           # Router Deployment + Service\n24:     ├── rbac/\n25:     │   └── workloadmanager.yaml        # WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n26:     ├── rbac-router.yaml                # Optional Router RBAC\n27:     └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n28: ```\n29: \n30: ### Component Diagram\n31: \n32: ```\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                    Helm Chart (agentcube)                        │\n35: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n36:                               │\n37:                               │ helm install/upgrade\n38:                               ▼\n39: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                   Kubernetes Cluster                             │\n41: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐ │\n42: │  │     Router       │  │ WorkloadManager  │  │   Volcano     │ │\n43: │  │  Deployment      │  │   Deployment     │  │   Scheduler   │ │\n44: │  │  + Service       │  │   + Service      │  │  (optional)   │ │\n45: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └───────────────┘ │\n46: │           │                      │                               │\n47: │           └──────────┬───────────┘                               │\n48: │                      │                                           │\n49: │           ┌──────────▼───────────┐                               │\n50: │           │   Redis Secret        │                               │\n51: │           │   (password store)    │                               │\n52: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n53: │                                                                   │\n54: │           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n55: │           │   RBAC Resources      │                               │\n56: │           │   (SA, Role, Binding) │                               │\n57: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n58: │                                                                   │\n59: │           ┌──────────────────────┐                               │\n60: │           │      CRDs             │                               │\n61: │           │  agentruntimes,       │                               │\n62: │           │  codeinterpreters     │                               │\n63: │           └───────────────────────┘                               │\n64: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ### Integration Points\n68: \n69: - **Redis**: External dependency for session storage (address/password from values)\n70: - **Volcano Scheduler**: Optional component for advanced scheduling\n71: - **RBAC**: WorkloadManager requires cluster-wide permissions; Router RBAC is optional\n72: - **CRDs**: AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n73: \n74: ## Data Structures\n75: \n76: ### Chart.yaml Metadata\n77: \n78: ```yaml\n79: apiVersion: v1\n80: name: agentcube\n81: description: A Helm chart for AgentCube\n82: version: 0.1.0\n83: appVersion: \"1.0.0\"\n84: keywords:\n85:   - agent\n86:   - sandbox\n87:   - kubernetes\n88:   - volcano\n89: maintainers:\n90:   - name: Volcano Authors\n91:     email: volcano-sh@googlegroups.com\n92: home: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n93: sources:\n94:   - https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ### values.yaml Configuration Tree\n98: \n99: ```yaml\n100: # Global settings\n101: imagePullSecrets: []\n102: nameOverride: \"\"\n103: fullnameOverride: \"\"\n104: \n105: # Redis configuration (required)\n106: redis:\n107:   addr: \"\"           # Required: Redis address (e.g., \"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\")\n108:   password: \"\"       # Optional: Redis password for authentication\n109: \n110: # Router component\n111: router:\n112:   replicas: 1\n113:   image:\n114:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router\n115:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n116:     tag: \"latest\"\n117:   service:\n118:     type: ClusterIP\n119:     port: 8080\n120:     targetPort: 8080\n121:   resources:\n122:     limits:\n123:       cpu: 500m\n124:       memory: 512Mi\n125:     requests:\n126:       cpu: 100m\n127:       memory: 128Mi\n128:   config: {}                      # Additional container configuration\n129:   extraEnv: []                    # Additional environment variables\n130:   serviceAccountName: \"\"          # Empty for default/auto-generated\n131:   rbac:\n132:     create: false                 # Disable RBAC by default\n133: \n134: # WorkloadManager component\n135: workloadmanager:\n136:   replicas: 1\n137:   image:\n138:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager\n139:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n140:     tag: \"latest\"\n141:   service:\n142:     type: ClusterIP\n143:     port: 8080\n144:   resources:\n145:     limits:\n146:       cpu: 500m\n147:       memory: 512Mi\n148:     requests:\n149:       cpu: 100m\n150:       memory: 128Mi\n151:   extraEnv: []                    # Additional environment variables\n152: \n153: # Volcano Scheduler (optional)\n154: volcano:\n155:   scheduler:\n156:     enabled: false                # Disabled by default\n157:     replicas: 1\n158:     image:\n159:       repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler\n160:       pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n161:       tag: \"latest\"\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ### Environment Variables\n165: \n166: | Variable | Component | Description | Source |\n167: |----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n168: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Namespace from downward API | `fieldRef: metadata.namespace` |\n169: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis connection address | `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}` |\n170: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis authentication | `Secret {{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password` |\n171: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | Constructed: `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}` |\n172: \n173: ## API Contracts\n174: \n175: ### Template Contracts\n176: \n177: #### WorkloadManager Deployment\n178: \n179: ```yaml\n180: apiVersion: apps/v1\n181: kind: Deployment\n182: metadata:\n183:   name: workloadmanager\n184:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n185:   labels:\n186:     app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager\n187:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n188: spec:\n189:   replicas: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}\n190:   selector:\n191:     matchLabels:\n192:       app: workloadmanager\n193:   template:\n194:     metadata:\n195:       labels:\n196:         app: workloadmanager\n197:     spec:\n198:       serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\n199:       containers:\n200:       - name: workloadmanager\n201:         image: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\n202:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}\n203:         args:\n204:         - --port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n205:         - --runtime-class-name=\n206:         env:\n207:         - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n208:           valueFrom:\n209:             fieldRef:\n210:               fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n211:         - name: REDIS_ADDR\n212:           value: {{ .Values.redis.addr }}\n213:         - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n214:           valueFrom:\n215:             secretKeyRef:\n216:               name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis\n217:               key: password\n218:         - name: {{ .name }}\n219:           value: {{ .value }}\n220:         # ... extraEnv injected here\n221:         ports:\n222:         - name: http\n223:           containerPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\n224:           protocol: TCP\n225:         livenessProbe:\n226:           httpGet:\n227:             path: /health\n228:             port: http\n229:           initialDelaySeconds: 10\n230:           periodSeconds: 10\n231:         readinessProbe:\n232:           httpGet:\n233:             path: /health\n234:             port: http\n235:           initialDelaySeconds: 5\n236:           periodSeconds: 5\n237:         resources: {{ toYaml .Values.workloadmanager.resources | nindent 10 }}\n238: ```\n239: \n240: #### Router Deployment\n241: \n242: ```yaml\n243: apiVersion: apps/v1\n244: kind: Deployment\n245: metadata:\n246:   name: agentcube-router\n247:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n248:   labels:\n249:     app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router\n250:     app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n251: spec:\n252:   replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicas }}\n253:   selector:\n254:     matchLabels:\n255:       app: agentcube-router\n256:   template:\n257:     metadata:\n258:       labels:\n259:         app: agentcube-router\n260:     spec:\n261:       {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n262:       serviceAccountName: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n263:       {{- end }}\n264:       containers:\n265:       - name: agentcube-router\n266:         image: {{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\n267:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n268:         args:\n269:         - --port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n270:         - --debug\n271:         env:\n272:         - name: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n273:           valueFrom:\n274:             fieldRef:\n275:               fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n276:         - name: REDIS_ADDR\n277:           value: {{ .Values.redis.addr }}\n278:         - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n279:           valueFrom:\n280:             secretKeyRef:\n281:               name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis\n282:               key: password\n283:         - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n284:           value: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"\n285:         # ... extraEnv injected here\n286:         ports:\n287:         - name: http\n288:           containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}\n289:           protocol: TCP\n290:         livenessProbe:\n291:           httpGet:\n292:             path: /health/live\n293:             port: http\n294:           initialDelaySeconds: 1\n295:           periodSeconds: 2\n296:         readinessProbe:\n297:           httpGet:\n298:             path: /health/ready\n299:             port: http\n300:           initialDelaySeconds: 1\n301:           periodSeconds: 2\n302:         resources: {{ toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 10 }}\n303: ```\n304: \n305: #### WorkloadManager RBAC\n306: \n307: ```yaml\n308: # ServiceAccount\n309: apiVersion: v1\n310: kind: ServiceAccount\n311: metadata:\n312:   name: workloadmanager\n313:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n314: \n315: # ClusterRole\n316: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n317: kind: ClusterRole\n318: metadata:\n319:   name: workloadmanager\n320: rules:\n321: # Sandbox management\n322: - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n323:   resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n324:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n325: \n326: # Extension resources\n327: - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n328:   resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n329:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n330: \n331: # Warm pool status update\n332: - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n333:   resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n334:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n335: \n336: # CodeInterpreter management\n337: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n338:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n339:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n340: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n341:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n342:   verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n343: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n344:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n345:   verbs: [\"update\"]\n346: \n347: # AgentRuntime management\n348: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n349:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n350:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n351: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n352:   resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n353:   verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n354: \n355: # Pod read access\n356: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n357:   resources: [\"pods\"]\n358:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n359: \n360: # Token review for authentication\n361: - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n362:   resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n363:   verbs: [\"create\"]\n364: \n365: # Secret management\n366: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n367:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n368:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n369: \n370: # ClusterRoleBinding\n371: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n372: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n373: metadata:\n374:   name: workloadmanager\n375: roleRef:\n376:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n377:   kind: ClusterRole\n378:   name: workloadmanager\n379: subjects:\n380: - kind: ServiceAccount\n381:   name: workloadmanager\n382:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n383: ```\n384: \n385: #### Router RBAC (Optional)\n386: \n387: Rendered only when `router.rbac.create: true`:\n388: \n389: ```yaml\n390: # ServiceAccount\n391: apiVersion: v1\n392: kind: ServiceAccount\n393: metadata:\n394:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n395:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n396: \n397: # Role (namespace-scoped)\n398: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n399: kind: Role\n400: metadata:\n401:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n402:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n403: rules:\n404: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n405:   resources: [\"secrets\"]\n406:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n407: \n408: # RoleBinding\n409: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n410: kind: RoleBinding\n411: metadata:\n412:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n413:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n414: roleRef:\n415:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n416:   kind: Role\n417:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n418: subjects:\n419: - kind: ServiceAccount\n420:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}\n421:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n422: ```\n423: \n424: #### Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n425: \n426: Rendered only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`:\n427: \n428: ```yaml\n429: # ServiceAccount\n430: apiVersion: v1\n431: kind: ServiceAccount\n432: metadata:\n433:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n434: \n435: # ConfigMap\n436: apiVersion: v1\n437: kind: ConfigMap\n438: metadata:\n439:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap\n440: data:\n441:   agent-scheduler.conf: |\n442:     actions: \"allocate\"\n443:     tiers:\n444:     - plugins:\n445:       - name: predicates\n446:       - name: nodeorder\n447: \n448: # ClusterRole with comprehensive scheduling permissions\n449: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n450: kind: ClusterRole\n451: metadata:\n452:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n453: rules:\n454: # CRD management\n455: - apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]\n456:   resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]\n457:   verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n458: \n459: # Core resources\n460: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n461:   resources: [\"events\", \"pods\", \"pods/status\", \"pods/binding\"]\n462:   verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n463: # ... (additional pod-related permissions)\n464: \n465: # Deployment\n466: apiVersion: apps/v1\n467: kind: Deployment\n468: metadata:\n469:   name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n470: spec:\n471:   replicas: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas }}\n472:   template:\n473:     spec:\n474:       serviceAccountName: volcano-agent-scheduler\n475:       containers:\n476:       - name: volcano-agent-scheduler\n477:         image: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.image.tag }}\n478:         args:\n479:         - --scheduler-name=agent-scheduler\n480:         - --config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf\n481:         securityContext:\n482:           runAsNonRoot: true\n483:           runAsUser: 1000\n484:         volumeMounts:\n485:         - name: config\n486:           mountPath: /config\n487:         - name: empty\n488:           mountPath: /emptydir\n489:       volumes:\n490:       - name: config\n491:         configMap:\n492:           name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap\n493:       - name: empty\n494:         emptyDir: {}\n495: ```\n496: \n497: ### CRD Definitions\n498: \n499: #### AgentRuntime CRD\n500: \n501: ```yaml\n502: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n503: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n504: metadata:\n505:   name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n506: spec:\n507:   group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n508:   names:\n509:     kind: AgentRuntime\n510:     plural: agentruntimes\n511:     shortNames: [ar]\n512:     singular: agentruntime\n513:   scope: Namespaced\n514:   versions:\n515:   - name: v1alpha1\n516:     served: true\n517:     storage: true\n518:     additionalPrinterColumns:\n519:     - name: NAME\n520:       type: string\n521:       jsonPath: .metadata.name\n522:     - name: PHASE\n523:       type: string\n524:       jsonPath: .status.phase\n525:     - name: SANDBOX\n526:       type: string\n527:       jsonPath: .status.sandboxRef.name\n528:     - name: AGE\n529:       type: date\n530:       jsonPath: .metadata.creationTimestamp\n531:     schema:\n532:       openAPIV3Schema:\n533:         type: object\n534:         properties:\n535:           spec:\n536:             required:\n537:             - maxSessionDuration\n538:             - podTemplate\n539:             - sessionTimeout\n540:             - targetPort\n541:             properties:\n542:               maxSessionDuration:\n543:                 type: string\n544:                 default: \"8h\"\n545:               sessionTimeout:\n546:                 type: string\n547:                 default: \"15m\"\n548:               targetPort:\n549:                 type: array\n550:                 items:\n551:                   type: object\n552:                   required: [port, protocol]\n553:                   properties:\n554:                     port:\n555:                       type: integer\n556:                     protocol:\n557:                       type: string\n558:                       enum: [HTTP, HTTPS]\n559:               podTemplate:\n560:                 type: object\n561:                 # Full PodSpec-like schema\n562: ```\n563: \n564: #### CodeInterpreter CRD\n565: \n566: ```yaml\n567: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n568: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n569: metadata:\n570:   name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n571: spec:\n572:   group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n573:   names:\n574:     kind: CodeInterpreter\n575:     plural: codeinterpreters\n576:     shortNames: [ci]\n577:     singular: codeinterpreter\n578:   scope: Namespaced\n579:   versions:\n580:   - name: v1alpha1\n581:     served: true\n582:     storage: true\n583:     subresources:\n584:       status: {}\n585:     schema:\n586:       openAPIV3Schema:\n587:         type: object\n588:         properties:\n589:           spec:\n590:             required: [template]\n591:             properties:\n592:               authMode:\n593:                 type: string\n594:                 enum: [picod, none]\n595:                 default: picod\n596:               maxSessionDuration:\n597:                 type: string\n598:                 default: \"8h\"\n599:               sessionTimeout:\n600:                 type: string\n601:                 default: \"15m\"\n602:               warmPoolSize:\n603:                 type: integer\n604:                 format: int32\n605:               template:\n606:                 type: object\n607:                 # Container template schema\n608: ```\n609: \n610: ## Error Handling\n611: \n612: ### Chart Validation Errors\n613: \n614: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n615: |-------|-----------|---------|\n616: | Chart validation failure | 1 | `helm lint failed: {detail}` |\n617: | Template render failure | 1 | `helm template failed: {detail}` |\n618: | CRD installation failure | 1 | `Failed to install CRD: {detail}` |\n619: | Redis address not provided | 1 | `redis.addr is required in values` |\n620: | Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | `YAML parse error in {file}: {detail}` |\n621: \n622: ### Runtime Errors\n623: \n624: | Error | Component | Recovery |\n625: |-------|-----------|----------|\n626: | Redis connection refused | Router, WorkloadManager | Retry with exponential backoff |\n627: | Invalid Redis password | Router, WorkloadManager | Log error, fail health check |\n628: | RBAC permission denied | WorkloadManager | Log error, fail reconciliation |\n629: | CRD not found | All components | Fail startup, require manual CRD install |\n630: \n631: ## Testing Strategy\n632: \n633: ### Unit Tests\n634: \n635: **Location**: `manifests/charts/base/tests/` (to be created)\n636: \n637: ```yaml\n638: # tests/workloadmanager_test.yaml\n639: suite: WorkloadManager Deployment tests\n640: tests:\n641:   - it: creates Deployment with correct metadata\n642:     asserts:\n643:       - hasDocuments:\n644:           count: 1\n645:         documentIndex: 0\n646:         isKind:\n647:           of: Deployment\n648:       - equal:\n649:           path: metadata.name\n650:           value: workloadmanager\n651: \n652:   - it: sets replicas from values\n653:     set:\n654:       workloadmanager.replicas: 3\n655:     asserts:\n656:       - equal:\n657:           path: spec.replicas\n658:           value: 3\n659: \n660:   - it: injects correct environment variables\n661:     asserts:\n662:       - contains:\n663:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].env\n664:           content:\n665:             name: REDIS_ADDR\n666:             value: \"redis.default.svc.cluster.local:6379\"\n667: \n668:   - it: configures liveness probe correctly\n669:     asserts:\n670:       - equal:\n671:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].livenessProbe.httpGet.path\n672:           value: /health\n673:       - equal:\n674:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].livenessProbe.initialDelaySeconds\n675:           value: 10\n676: \n677:   - it: applies resource limits from values\n678:     set:\n679:       workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 1000m\n680:       workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 1Gi\n681:     asserts:\n682:       - equal:\n683:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.limits.cpu\n684:           value: 1000m\n685: ```\n686: \n687: ### Integration Tests\n688: \n689: **Command**: `helm template test manifests/charts/base`\n690: \n691: Verify:\n692: 1. All templates render without errors\n693: 2. Generated YAML is valid\n694: 3. Conditional resources respect flags\n695: 4. Values overrides work correctly\n696: \n697: **Command**: `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n698: \n699: Verify:\n700: 1. No linting errors or warnings\n701: 2. Chart structure is valid\n702: 3. All required files present\n703: \n704: ### E2E Tests\n705: \n706: **Scenario**: Full chart installation in Kind cluster\n707: \n708: ```bash\n709: # Create Kind cluster\n710: kind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n711: \n712: # Install chart\n713: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n714:   --namespace agentcube \\\n715:   --create-namespace \\\n716:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n717:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n718:   --wait\n719: \n720: # Verify deployments are ready\n721: kubectl wait deployment/workloadmanager --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n722: kubectl wait deployment/agentcube-router --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n723: \n724: # Verify services are created\n725: kubectl get svc -n agentcube\n726: \n727: # Test with optional components\n728: helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n729:   --namespace agentcube \\\n730:   --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true \\\n731:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n732:   --wait\n733: \n734: # Verify optional components\n735: kubectl wait deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler --for=condition=Available --namespace=agentcube --timeout=2m\n736: kubectl get clusterrole/workloadmanager\n737: kubectl get role/agentcube-router --namespace=agentcube\n738: \n739: # Cleanup\n740: kind delete cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n741: ```\n742: \n743: ## Dependencies\n744: \n745: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n746: |---------|---------|---------|\n747: | Helm | ≥3.0.0 | Chart packaging and deployment |\n748: | Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | API compatibility |\n749: | Redis | Any | External dependency (session storage) |\n750: | Volcano | Optional | Advanced scheduling (if enabled) |\n751: \n752: ## File Structure\n753: \n754: ```\n755: manifests/\n756: └── charts/\n757:     └── base/\n758:         ├── Chart.yaml                    # REQUIRED: Chart metadata\n759:         ├── values.yaml                   # REQUIRED: Default configuration\n760:         ├── .helmignore                   # REQUIRED: Packaging exclusions\n761:         ├── crds/\n762:         │   ├── agentruntime.yaml         # EXISTING: AgentRuntime CRD\n763:         │   └── codeinterpreter.yaml      # NEW: CodeInterpreter CRD\n764:         └── templates/\n765:             ├── _helpers.tpl              # Helper templates\n766:             ├── redis-secret.yaml         # Redis password Secret\n767:             ├── workloadmanager.yaml      # WorkloadManager Deployment + Service\n768:             ├── agentcube-router.yaml     # Router Deployment + Service\n769:             ├── rbac/\n770:             │   └── workloadmanager.yaml  # WorkloadManager RBAC\n771:             ├── rbac-router.yaml          # Optional Router RBAC\n772:             └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano Scheduler\n773: ```\n774: \n775: ## Multi-Environment Support\n776: \n777: ### Development Environment\n778: \n779: ```yaml\n780: # values-dev.yaml\n781: router:\n782:   replicas: 1\n783:   resources:\n784:     limits:\n785:       cpu: 250m\n786:       memory: 256Mi\n787:     requests:\n788:       cpu: 50m\n789:       memory: 64Mi\n790: \n791: workloadmanager:\n792:   replicas: 1\n793:   resources:\n794:     limits:\n795:       cpu: 250m\n796:       memory: 256Mi\n797:     requests:\n798:       cpu: 50m\n799:       memory: 64Mi\n800: \n801: volcano:\n802:   scheduler:\n803:     enabled: false\n804: ```\n805: \n806: ### Production Environment\n807: \n808: ```yaml\n809: # values-prod.yaml\n810: router:\n811:   replicas: 3\n812:   resources:\n813:     limits:\n814:       cpu: 1000m\n815:       memory: 1Gi\n816:     requests:\n817:       cpu: 200m\n818:       memory: 256Mi\n819: \n820: workloadmanager:\n821:   replicas: 2\n822:   resources:\n823:     limits:\n824:       cpu: 1000m\n825:       memory: 1Gi\n826:     requests:\n827:       cpu: 200m\n828:       memory: 256Mi\n829: \n830: volcano:\n831:   scheduler:\n832:     enabled: true\n833:     replicas: 2\n834: ```\n835: \n836: ### Usage\n837: \n838: ```bash\n839: # Development\n840: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base -f values-dev.yaml \\\n841:   --set redis.addr=redis-dev:6379\n842: \n843: # Production\n844: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base -f values-prod.yaml \\\n845:   --set redis.addr=redis-prod:6379\n846: \n847: # Custom image registry\n848: helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n849:   --set router.image.repository=myregistry.com/agentcube-router \\\n850:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=myregistry.com/workloadmanager\n851: ```\n852: \n853: ## Acceptance Checklist\n854: \n855: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` — Chart metadata with correct apiVersion, name, version\n856: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` — Complete configuration tree for all components\n857: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with correct env/probes\n858: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n859: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n860: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` — Conditional Router RBAC\n861: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — Conditional Volcano Scheduler\n862: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml` — Redis password Secret\n863: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml` — AgentRuntime CRD (existing, verify completeness)\n864: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml` — CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n865: - [ ] `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore` — Ignore patterns for packaging\n866: - [ ] `helm lint` passes without errors\n867: - [ ] `helm template` generates valid YAML\n868: - [ ] `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n869: - [ ] Optional components render correctly when enabled/disabled\n870: - [ ] Values overrides work correctly for multi-environment support\n871: \n872: ## Open Questions\n873: \n874: 1. **External Redis Operator Integration**: Should the chart support automatic Redis provisioning via Redis Operator (e.g., Spotahome, OperatorHub)?\n875: \n876: 2. **Monitoring and Logging**: Should Prometheus scrape annotations, ServiceMonitor CRs, and Fluentd/ELK integration be included in the chart?\n877: \n878: 3. **Multi-Cluster Deployment**: Should the chart support deployment across multiple Kubernetes clusters with shared Redis backend?\n879: \n880: 4. **Default Values for Development**: Should the chart include a `values-dev.yaml` file with development-appropriate defaults out of the box?\n881: \n882: 5. **Ingress Configuration**: Should an Ingress resource be added for external access to Router and WorkloadManager services?\n883: \n884: 6. **Pod Disruption Budgets**: Should PDBs be configured for production deployments to ensure availability during node maintenance?\n\n(End of file - total 884 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-030 Helm Chart Templates and Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the AgentCube Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`). The chart packages and deploys all AgentCube control plane components including Router, WorkloadManager, and optional Volcano Agent Scheduler with support for multi-environment configurations.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata (apiVersion, name, version)\n├── values.yaml                         # Configuration values tree\n├── .helmignore                         # Packaging exclusion patterns\n├── crds/\n│   ├── agentruntime.yaml               # AgentRuntime CRD (existing)\n│   └── codeinterpreter.yaml            # CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n└── templates/\n    ├── _helpers.tpl                    # Template helper functions","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/design.md","time":{"start":1775879565030,"end":1775879565058}}}}
